    <note type="biography">
        <p>German physician and naturalist. Completed a dissertation on earthworms in Berlin in 1842; wrote and illustrated a monograph on earthworms in 1845. In 1844, accompanied Prince Waldemar of Prussia as a personal physician on an expedition to India; killed in battle after the outbreak of a war with the Sikhs.</p></note>
